            <p facs="#facs_76_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>Monsieur M r de
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>¼63.
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>bringing must be the first step, in order tõavid the situation of congress, of which
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>I was speaking. Symbols have the character of opening up reality even to the most lnimitive mind,
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>and they have just the function to do this to all minds—the most lrimitive and the most sophisticated.
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>They are common to every
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/> [1] group and age. Therefore if we prevent our children from
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>receiving these symbols as early as they can be exposed to the opening power of Abbols, then we are
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>responsible (even if it is the best will) for having produced a vacuum. And this vacuum is hard to
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>be filled later on. These early symbols, early payers, early litergical experiences, early species
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>about God and the Christ, which are in a very primitive form going on, have by their symbolic power
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>nevertheless the possibility of opening up levels of reality which otherwise would never be opened.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_76_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>We don't prevent our children from singing very early, and hearing music very early
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>and considering nature very early, before a full understanding of all this. The symbols, in this] case
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>the artistic symbols, PRECEDE the understanding, the FULL understanding. And let me add:
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>they precede the understanding to the last days of our life—great works of art are inexhaustible.
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>So we should start with the religious symbol s also, as early as possible, where words and visions
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>are given to the child already.
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>But now the great problem arises: these symbols have altogether a meaning in the realm
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_76_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>of the symbolic. But the child is not able to distinguish the Hoibolic from the non-symbolic
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>and
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>and takes the symbol’s literally, takes everything liberal, symbolic. The child is here Hepeating
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>the development of mankind, as far as we can see it back. In this fortopment, the distinction
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>dʼaccembre. Je nʼai pas
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>le prêter de
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>dʼune manière beaucoup de vous
               <lb facs="#facs_76_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼavoir lʼautre vie de ses
